  "text": "In UTEX 2973, the trend in expression patterns was similar to that in Synechocystis (Fig. 5B) . However, the overall expression levels of eYFP measured in UTEX 2973 were significantly higher than in Synechocystis. Pcpc560 was increased by 30%, while PrnpB showed a 20-fold increase in expression relative to Synechocystis. The relative expression strength of PpsbA2L was also higher than in Synechocystis, and second only to Pcpc560 in UTEX 2973. As promoters derived from PpsbA are responsive to increasing light levels [CITATION_1] , the increased levels of expression for PpsbA2L may be associated with the higher light intensities used for growing UTEX 2973 compared to Synechocystis.",
